MATRIARCHY// Yesterday marked 83 years for The Oma, which we celebrated with pound cake and fire. To use the words fierce or badass to describe her seems trite, not enough, it's like bringing a stick of butter to a knife fight. Wars, hunger, idiotic husbands, sexist corporate culture, she has verily surmounted them all and come out laughing. She's the beacon, for me, my daughter, and now my daughter's daughter. She's how we know to #amplifythelight.

Good golly if I could start each day with a dashi egg and SPAM sandwich, I might finally become a perfect human.

"Natasha is not charmed by nature. She is not nurturing, maternal, faithful, self-sacrificing, sympathetic, or inherently good. She has an accent. She pours herself into a tight dress and packs a switchblade nail file. She is not a nest builder and she doesn't cry. She cracks jokes at the expense of others. She wears disguises. She's a saboteur! What goes on in her private life we'll never know for sure, but with the way she's always blowing up lakes and mountains, you can be sure something's happening behind closed doors. I imagine Natasha's face was her training ground for future battles. She doesn't accept that the mountain belongs there and it's not her place to blow it up. She doesn't accept the face God gave her and proceeds to pluck out the eyebrow hairs one by one and paint the peach lids brilliant blue. And I'm guessing the hair is dyed too. Natasha does not say take me as I am. She says take me as I dream myself. Natasha dominates nature. She carves out reality in a distinctly female way. Men build; women alter. We don't create fate, we manipulate it. Whatever happened to Natasha in retribution for her defiance we will never know. But she'll pay the price for her ambition, believe it. She'll be sorry, but right now she's not sorry at all."

—Lisa Crystal Carver, @carver9963 founder of the raunchy fanzine, Rollerderby. 

Happy #internationalwomensday
To all my Natashas. 🖤💜

What if I said: AMALFI COAST, let's go eat?!?!?

Then what if you said: yes let's.

I'm doing a little trip with my friends (literal friends, we went to high school together) at @piquetravel and you should come. 

This is a foodist trip down the coast of Italy, scooting around the boot to pop into Croatia's Dalmatian Coast, and all the wine that implies. There might be limoncello groves, there will be so much prosciutto tasting that we'll have to create a ham index, and it all happens with benefit of a floating boutique hotel (it's a 🚢, which I swore I would never do but I've been wooed because then I don't have to keep repacking.)

It happens this fall, and this is not a huge group thing, so if you think you might want to nerd out with me over fish markets, fruit brandies, island wineries, and Italian coffee cafe culture, don't dally. Pop over for details and pricing, timing is Sept 27-Oct 4. 

Then: we can talk about Japan in 2024!!

It was spring of 2018, I was at The Lynhall to moderate a cooking class with Raghavan. Before it started, he pulled me aside and we had a hug before he said, "I have to tell you that I will be teaching this class sitting down. I recently found out I have cancer, but we're not going to make a big thing about it." Then he squeezed my arm and we went to work. 

He spun stories, he brought light, punctuating saturated moments with that little giggle: a gift and an invitation to be in it together. I watched the audience rapt with his voice and his lessons, and I watched him, knowing there was a new frightful path ahead of him,  never afraid to give of himself. 

Always teaching. ♥️

We were so lucky to sit with you all these years, beautiful man. @raghavaniyer you made us better.

Untethered 💔 Just before my birthday in January, my mom found out she had Leukemia. Just before her birthday in February, Brigitte von Haken decided she would rather live full and juiced days instead of chasing any chemo dreams. They gave us six months and we called it The Long Goodbye. We've spent that time telling stories, finding long lost denim dresses, bouncing babies on The Oma's knee, and just luxuriating in each other's memories and laughter. We fed and were fed.

She was unafraid of death, preferring a handshake understanding, with a firm grip. It was, she said, what put living into practice and gave love its softest parts. She taught me that the hard was good and that sorrow was not an ending, but a beginning of gratitude. 

After spending years in church choirs and reading endless texts, she also decided that heaven wasn't for her. Who wants to hang around eternity with a bunch of people who all think alike? She just wanted to be free. 

This morning, under my watch, as the sun rose, she became the wind. Free to roam the spectacular spectacular. 

She took her leave on a 13th, a significant number in our family, which remains: lucky.

Gratitude ♥️ The messages and outpouring of love has been so lifting this week, I am humbled by all of you, and truly hope to acknowledge and thank you all. 

I'd really love to thank everyone who has had to cover for me these last six months, who stepped in when I had to run to Oma, or gave me a pass when I had to bail. Big shout out to @modistbrewing who not only understood when I had to cancel last minute, but then donated money for blood. 

Her official obit is linked in my bio, and it's long, but not long enough. In lieu of flowers we're asking to send cash (or blood!) to the Memorial Blood Centers @memorialbldctrs, also linked in my bio. If it weren't for the transfusions she received, we wouldn't have had The Long Goodbye. Which meant everything. ♥️🩸 #donateblood

Solstice 🌞 We five who loved her most and knew her best have laid her in fire today. Onward! ♥️ This passage from Mexican poet and Nobel laureate Octavio Paz is what we sent with her:

"Love is not eternity; nor is it the time of calendars and watches, successive time. The time of love is neither great nor small; it is the perception of all times, of all lives, in a single moment. It does not free us from death but makes us see it face to face ... We are the theater of the embrace of opposites and of their dissolution, resolved in a single note that is not affirmation or negation, but acceptance ... The presence that dissolves into splendor, pure vitality, a heartbeat of time."

📷: @eliesajohnson ♥️

Dishers may know this story. My Oma was a great cook, and when we traveled back to Michigan to see her, she would make the most unusual things: wildly bright pink potato salad, a striped cake she called kalte pracht, schmantbonbons wrapped in wax paper. My Opa didn't think anyone would want her dog-eared, note-scribbled, stained page Baltisches Kochbuch, so after she died he donated her copy. Just sent it out into the universe with all her conversions and notes and magic. So, whenever I go into an antique store or thrifty, I look for a BK with Elfriede von Haken on the front page. She might still come back to me. Today, I found my own mother's copy in my book inheritance. It's full of her own scribbles and translations, and I've cooked from it with her before. But only today did I realize on the first page, in the hand I perpetually seek, it says Viel glück! Mami (Much luck! Mommy). It feels like we three cooks are bound once again. ♥️

Friday night, at a training dinner for the opening of @porzanasteaks , I held back on jamming my face full of crab riddled pasta because we had some serious steaks coming in the next course. 

But, Friday had other plans as the fire alarm went off, the kitchen and dining room filled with smoke, and the fire brigade showed up. No one was hurt, nothing burned down, but the kitchen was closed. @meganmluedtke, @billsummerville, and @sippinonhennessy calmly walked around gifting glasses of v. nice bubbles, and anyone left removed ourselves to the @floraroommpls for drinks and boxes of gratis Pizza Luce. A spectacular save, and not a bad night really at all. 

I heard that last night's service was plagued with AC issues, and it made me think back to all the restaurant openings in my life, which is a lot. This tool in your hands often gives us the power to create tiny moments of perfection and amplify that as a standard. But neither is that reality, nor is it humanity, and I will die on the hill that: restaurants are made of people (with all the flaws that implies). Opening a restaurant, working a restaurant, creating a small business is a practice, and it differs every day by who decides to really show up. I don't have a stunning picture of a beautiful steak, but I do have a picture of teamwork and hospitality. And a notion that glitter doesn't actually shine until you shake it and move it a bit. ✨

For the first time since 1977, I don't have a key to this house. It's not so much about the memories, the teenage ballyhoo on the trampoline in the back yard, the epic sleepovers, my own kids dangling from the same trees I climbed, mowing the same winding paths in the fallen leaves: those bricks built us and we stay built. What I struggled with this week, was that over all those years, no matter how dented or askew my life was, I could come back to this place, time after time. And sitting around the kitchen table, I could become whole again. I have never found that elsewhere in the world. Of course that magic didn't come from the walls, though they contained the woman who wove it, so it's hard not to believe something lingers. The closing of this house is also the last task assigned to me, and having completed it this morning, the finality I've probably been running from, has fused to my bones. And now I continue the work of creating the same while we sally forth, as sunshine yellow foundations bid us: ever onward. ♥️🏡

Guys, I did a thing. 

Some of you know that I think the world is best when all of our kooky weird vibes, our idiosyncratic behaviors, and unique vibrations all come together. Keep your singularities, for me the blend is the thing. 

Earlier this year I sat with James Jefferson at @justuswhiskey and we sipped our way through many barrels of American single malt while pulling out the best flavors and the truest golden notes so that we might blend them all together to create something cool, something that sings, something that is both noisy and harmonious. 

I think we did it? There's a lilt of buttered toast, and a wink of baking spice, but also a wee mouth slap of pepper  IMHO. Kind of like a two-finger whistle in a crowded room (😉). 

It's in a bottle!! SMarch Select is not shy, 121 proof, and she's now available to pick up at the distillery. This is a very limited run, so don't waffle. I am not earning dollars from this, but we are making a donation to the @memorialbldctrs in my mom's name. And I have grabbed a few bottles that I'll be dropping into select silent auctions for charities. 

Drink it like this: 3 fingers + 1 rock 🥃♥️

POV: You can't stop thinking about the Roman Empire, so you do something about it. Like walk 18.5K steps around The Eternal City sipping prosecco on rooftops, spritz in alleys, and officially kicking off  Ham Week. Also, the secret to kicking jet lag isn't carbs, it's carbs + guanciale. Not pictured: tiramisu on the Spanish steps because phone had a whammy on it. Tomorrow, we see dead people and get on a boat!

Guys, I got on a boat today. Tho I swore I never would, it's actually lovely so far. (Quick: last two moments in Rome were a tour of the Priscilla Catacombs and I did NOT steal any bones of popes, and the church of St. Clemens which had an excellent mosaic with shep) But now I'm at sea, dear friends, and my crew is killah. We had a gorgeous multi course dinner at the chef's table for the first night, then shut down the dance floor, as one does. Tomorrow: Sorrento and Limoncello. 🍋 #visinekills #zippermerge #italy

🍋🍋 SORRENTO 🍋🍋
Just a smidge in love with this lemon lit beauty. We visited a local family farm, where they make their own wine, grow olives, tomatoes, prosciutto and mama-recipe Limoncello. We lunched under their kiwi trees then hit the city for alleys full of cafes, leather jackets, and Limoncello bottles of a questionable nature (check stories 😉). We continued to lemon spritz it up on a Michelin starred patio, paid our respects to Mt. Vesuvius, and ended with a few spectacular pizzas. That's the og Napoli stuffed crust, btw, and there's HAM in there. Happy to report no one has fallen in yet. Next up Kotor, Montenegro. #italy #hamweek

🐱KOTOR, MONTENEGRO🐱

An actual country since 2006! Look it up! We passed into this calm and sunny bay off the Adriatic, and sought miracles from the Lady of the Rock before hitting up a small waterside eatery run by fisherman. The walled town of Kotor is run by cats, don't even try to argue. I did find an excellent tree friend tho. The local ham was OUTSTANDING, but we found ourselves at a restaurant that didn't live up to the hype. So we scurried to Konaba Scala Sante for 2nd dinner and begged for a save: cuttlefish black risotto and Croatian natural wine. We dubbed our server the King of Kotor and made it back to the ship just before it left. Trying really hard not to make that a theme. Check the stories for more! #moysters #loveshack #cannedblackolivetrigger

🏰 DUBROVNIK, CROATIA 🏰

Many know this white walled city as the place Game of Thrones was filmed, but for me it was giving Gondor. A perfectly balanced day which started with so many stairs, not sure why the tourist shops don't sell GoT branded knee braces. We left the city for a small family run restaurant where they shared their homemade grappa, and the black olive version haunts me even now. Changed my whole brain. Then they cooked us pecka, a Croatian specialty braise of octopus and meats that slow cooks in ash for the entire day. Rustic elegance under the olive trees on the patio. Back in the city, some went bar hopping, some relaxed, some took in the AzAmazing show, and some went to the Michelin starred @360dubrovnik for a fast three course stunner paired with local wines. Just a perfect day. Stories for more!

The last two days we really sealed the deal with two small producer winery visits. @barakawinery near the Croatian town of Sibenik was an elegant afternoon introduction to grapes we've never tasted before. Their small vineyard is so focused on their gorgeous and drinkable food wines, from grapes called babic and posip, which are not available in the US (yet, ahem @libationproject). The second day we went to the birthplace of Prosecco and it's not a small amount that I am in love with Katrin whose "micro, micro, micro, micro" vineyard @klin.vina is a one woman show. An actual Wine Queen, it's a thing, she blew our minds with regional history and pet-nat. And the best ham plate yet. We grocery shopped in Trieste for our final night Sundowner deck chair picnic on the bow of the boat, which I've decided is a new travel smarch tradition. Had nothing to do with drinking all those wines instead of hauling them home. #sheetofthecow #theshaggyincident #crotchspritz

And that's a wrap! Off the 🚢 back to life. Where should we go next you guys?!

I swore to the cool kids at @herbanwolfdeli that I would NOT eat my VooDoo sandwich in my car. Whoops. At least the Du Nord corned beef made it to my lunch date. The pickle pasta salad didn't even make it for the photo, friends. ♥️🥒 #sandwich

Ok @joansinthepark, I see you.  When you need a little lady-pampering, you'd be lucky to land here. Also: Susan Dunlop cooks with her full ♥️.

Quinoa with lobster.

9:44pm 10/21/23 @stephanie.a.meyer and I sneaked in and got the very last order of mushroom birria tacos on the very last night of @sookimimi. Nothing but ♥️ and 🔥 for what @annbkool has made and is making...LFG #unabashedhypewoman

As the months comes to a close, I just want to thank my buddy, @stephaniemarch and the whole crew at @mspmag for thinking of me for their special issue on my fab neighborhood, the North Loop of Minneapolis. There are so many wonderfully talented individuals in this area and I’m just proud to be among them. And gratitude for the amazing photography team who worked around my crazy schedule to make the cover shoot work. 

📷: @ackermangruber

Guys, I went into @velleemn in Old Town for a post-show quesadilla (as one does), but found they have a new menu of BREKKIE SANDWICHES! The most perfectly fluffy scrambled eggs under that cheese hug (for those of you weary of the souffle egg block) plus sausage and avocado on mine. Free parking in the building lot if you are too hungry to circle for a meter. #breakfast #sandwich

I'm kinda sorry you don't have this bacon, egg, cheese, (tots?) burrito wrapped in a scallion pancake from @saturdaydumplingco . BUT I'M MORE SAD THAT I DON'T. because I frickin inhaled it this morning. Get one next weekend if you know what's right in the world. 💗⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

Energy is real.

There's a whole new vibe on the 31st block of Uptown at @kimsuptown. Housemade spam and elegant salmon tartare: adventure and chill. It's a big fuggin beautiful sparkly loud rooted reverberating groovin' yes for me. 🦕💗

Read the First Bite on mspmag.com!

Friends, it's time to talk about JAPAN 2025! 

Wanna go see the Empire of the Sun with me? 🇯🇵⛩️ Not the movie, but the whole country? Last time I was there, in 2015, it fully changed me. These pics that @eliesajohnson took of our trip are a sliver of the amazing things we saw, ate, and drank while there.

I am going back with @piquetravel in the spring of 2025! And I'm planning a very fun, thrilling, relaxing, mind expanding trip with ramen alleys, fish markets, sake, whisky, sushi, so much 🍣 

There's a link in bio for a form where you can give me your email and we'll send you more info! This is a good thing to talk to your fam about over the TD table instead of politics IMHO. #japan #travel #foodtravel

Fellow Vixens (plus Comets, Cupids, Donners, and Blitzens, no Dashers, yes Dancers and Prancers), please report to me. I have found you no less than 12 local bars who have decked their halls and committed to being your Christmas Bar for 2023. Cups of Cheer raised in the general direction of all Fezziwigs!

🍜🚨BREAKING NOODS🚨🍜

Starting today, @yiavang70 re-launches his Slurp Noodle Bar pop-up at the @unionhmongkitchen space in @grazenorthloop. It had such a hot run last year popping up on Lake Street, and now it's back to warm your cold cold hearts with NEW TRICKS!

Hello Wonton Noodle Soup with fat little pork-stuffed wontons and a winning broth. 🥟

Welcome Tim-Tim Noodles with your spicy lamb Bolognese, named in honor of @thetimtruong 🔥

And salutations to the Duck Duck Quack bowl which plops salted duck egg butter on top of udon noodles with a pecorino cheese sauce for the cacio e pepe riff of the century. 🦆

Plus chicken leg salad, tofu soup, and more ... Open now! Fly, you fools!

So, @porzanasteaks did a little soft launch on brunch today and maybe if I hadn't been an instigator in a 9-bottle jingle basement birthday bubbles bash for @joyestellesummers last night, I might have ordered with more ... elegance? Bygones. Instead, this bacon egg and cheese sauce on brioche b🔥tch showed up and saved Sunday. Also a potato cheese hash brown cake situation in which the potatoes are more like a suggestion the cheese is thinking over. As one does. #brunch #northloopmpls #eggsandwich

However you made it through the darkest day, you did. My technique involves garlic chili paste and oyster sauce. Here's a little mantra as you climb back toward the light of the summer solstice: STOP DOING THE SAME SHIT THAT DOESN'T SERVE. #wintersolstice

Powerful full moon burn party last night. We set fire to medical bills, letters to the dead, garage projects, stubborn brothers, car accidents, hopeful gratitudes, and so many more things we released into the night sky to cleanse the year. 

We set forth with a benediction from Bukowski, and I encourage you to read it while staring at a fat juicy moon anytime one shows up in 2024:

 "If you're going to try, go all the way. Otherwise, don't even start. This could mean losing girlfriends, wives, relatives and maybe even your mind. It could mean not eating for three or four days. It could mean freezing on a park bench. It could mean jail. It could mean derision. It could mean mockery -- isolation. Isolation is the gift. All the others are a test of your endurance, of how much you really want to do it. And, you'll do it, despite rejection and the worst odds. And it will be better than anything else you can imagine. If you're going to try, go all the way. There is no other feeling like that. You will be alone with the gods, and the nights will flame with fire. You will ride life straight to perfect laughter. It's the only good fight there is." 🔥

Welcome to your 2024, the year of YES, AND. Happy New Year firebabies!! 🔥

Prime rib grilled cheese and bubbs at the Dirty H in Excelsior is peerless.
